					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah but there are some ways to get around that, or make better use of the third palette.<br /><br />Using sprites or a double wide latter would cut down to two palettes.<br /><br />Even better might be to keep the third palette and use that palette more often in the 'sky-surface' transition areas.  The dark brown patterning would have to move out of those immediate areas of course.  But you could round off in the corners and vertical ridging of the ladders and such.  Doesn't work everywhere as the background isn't always white.  But areas where it was made white could add to the detail and make better use of the palette instead of only for the ladders.</div>

					
